    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Underwater vehicles that maneuver without humans on board. These exist in two types: remotely operated underwater vehicles (ROVs), which are tethered to and controlled by a remote operator, and autonomous underwater vehicles (AUVs), which maneuver independently of direct operator input.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000106171/Ridao, P., et al., On the identification of non-linear models of unmanned underwater vehicles [...] (2004)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000106169/Remotely Operated Vehicles Committee of the Marine Technology Society [online] (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Duikboten die opereren zonder mensen aan boord. Ze bestaan in twee soorten: ROV's, dat wil zeggen duikboten die onbemand en zijn verbonden met operators die ze op afstand besturen, en autonome duikboten (AUV's), die onafhankelijk van directe input van een operator opereren.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
